During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed a range of topics. She highlighted the celebration of International Women's Day and the upcoming International Women of Courage Awards Ceremony hosted by First Lady Jill Biden and Secretary of State Antony Blinken. She also mentioned that President Biden's budget, which will be released the following day, aims to cut the deficit by nearly $3 trillion over the next 10 years. Jean-Pierre emphasized the administration's commitment to fiscal responsibility and ensuring that the wealthy and large corporations pay their fair share. She also addressed questions about police accountability, unemployment, the potential ban on TikTok, shortages of medical supplies, and the President's upcoming speech.